<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,906,2013]" box="[151,314,906,932]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,314,906,932]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brady &amp; Robertson" authorityYear="1885" box="[151,314,906,932]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,314,906,932]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Darwinulidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="547" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,906,2013]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">
Although 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pinto &amp; Kotzian" baseAuthorityYear="1961" box="[267,572,943,969]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Penthesilenula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis box="[267,572,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Penthesilenula brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is globally widespread, known from seven of the world’s zoogeographical regions (
<bibRefCitation author="Meisch, C. &amp; Smith, R. J. &amp; Martens, K." box="[248,462,979,1005]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" pagination="1 - 135" refId="ref14199" refString="Meisch, C., Smith, R. J. &amp; Martens, K. (2019) A subjective global checklist of the extant non-marine Ostracoda (Crustacea). European Journal of Taxonomy, 492, 1 - 135. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2019.492" type="journal article" year="2019">
Meisch 
<emphasis box="[339,395,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
), it has not been previously recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[908,1017,979,1005]" name="China" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">East Asia</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith &amp; Chang, 2022" authorityName="Smith &amp; Chang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1027,1250,979,1005]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gravata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1027,1250,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Vestalenula gravata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1257,1346,979,1005]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1257,1346,979,1005]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Vestalenula</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
and the new record of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pinto &amp; Kotzian" baseAuthorityYear="1961" box="[516,673,1015,1041]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Penthesilenula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis box="[516,673,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">P. brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
herein, bring the total of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brady &amp; Robertson" authorityYear="1885" box="[963,1129,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="535" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Darwinuloidea">Darwinuloidea</taxonomicName>
species known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1372,1436,1015,1041]" name="Japan" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Japan</collectingCountry>
to nine, representing almost a quarter of the total number of extant species in this superfamily. Three of these, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pinto &amp; Kotzian" baseAuthorityYear="1961" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Penthesilenula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">P. brasiliensis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Brady &amp; Robertson, 1870)" baseAuthorityName="Brady &amp; Robertson" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[295,863,1087,1113]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Darwinula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stevensoni">
<emphasis box="[295,542,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Darwinula stevensoni</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Brady, G. S. &amp; Robertson, D." box="[557,855,1087,1113]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref12389" refString="Brady, G. S. &amp; Robertson, D. (1870) The Ostracoda and Foraminifera of tidal rivers. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 4, 6, 1 - 31. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222937008696200" type="journal article" year="1870">Brady &amp; Robertson, 1870</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Menzel, 1916)" baseAuthorityName="Menzel" baseAuthorityYear="1916" box="[924,1389,1087,1114]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Microdarwinula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zimmeri">
<emphasis box="[924,1205,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Microdarwinula zimmeri</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Menzel, R." box="[1221,1382,1087,1114]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" pagination="486 - 489" refId="ref14254" refString="Menzel, R. (1916) Moosbewohnende Harpacticiden und Ostracoden aus Ost-Afrika. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, 11 (3), 486 - 489." type="journal article" year="1916">Menzel, 1916</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, are globally widespread, while two of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rossetti &amp; Martens" authorityYear="1998" box="[605,734,1123,1149]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[605,734,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Vestalenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Neale &amp; Victor" baseAuthorityYear="1978" box="[844,1042,1123,1149]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lundi">
<emphasis box="[844,1042,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Vestalenula lundi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Martens &amp; Rossetti" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[1104,1384,1123,1149]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="molopoensis">
<emphasis box="[1104,1384,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Vestalenula molopoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, are known from more than one zoogeographical region (
<bibRefCitation author="Meisch, C. &amp; Smith, R. J. &amp; Martens, K." box="[736,950,1159,1185]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" pagination="1 - 135" refId="ref14199" refString="Meisch, C., Smith, R. J. &amp; Martens, K. (2019) A subjective global checklist of the extant non-marine Ostracoda (Crustacea). European Journal of Taxonomy, 492, 1 - 135. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2019.492" type="journal article" year="2019">
Meisch 
<emphasis box="[827,883,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). The other four species, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">
<taxonomicName authority="Smith et al., 2006" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornelia">Vestalenula cornelia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith &amp; Chang, 2022" authorityName="Smith &amp; Chang" authorityYear="2022" box="[194,416,1195,1221]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gravata" status="sp. nov.">Vestalenula gravata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[422,511,1195,1221]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[422,511,1195,1221]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Straub" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[524,773,1195,1221]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cylindrica">
<emphasis box="[524,773,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Vestalenula cylindrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[825,994,1195,1221]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[825,954,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Vestalenula</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, may be endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[1221,1328,1195,1221]" name="China" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">East Asia</collectingCountry>
, although 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Straub" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[151,291,1231,1257]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cylindrica">
<emphasis box="[151,291,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">V. cylindrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known as fossils from elsewhere, and may represent a relic endemic (Smith 
<emphasis box="[1157,1212,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">et al.</emphasis>
2006; 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, R. J. &amp; Janz, H." pageId="17" pageNumber="546" pagination="217 - 241" refId="ref15638" refString="Smith, R. J. &amp; Janz, H. (2009) Recent ostracods of the superfamilies Cytheroidea and Darwinuloidea (Crustacea) from Lake Biwa, a Japanese ancient lake. Species Diversity, 14, 217 - 241. https: // doi. org / 10.12782 / specdiv. 14.217" type="journal article" year="2009">Smith &amp; Janz 2009</bibRefCitation>
). The small size and lack of a pigmented eye indicates that 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith &amp; Chang, 2022" authorityName="Smith &amp; Chang" authorityYear="2022" box="[876,1099,1267,1293]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gravata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[876,1099,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Vestalenula gravata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1106,1196,1267,1293]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1106,1196,1267,1293]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
may be a stygobiont, which was washed to the surface in heavy rains prior to collecting. The distributions of stygobionts can be difficult to determine as direct access to groundwater is usually limited, and thus it is plausible that 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith &amp; Chang, 2022" authorityName="Smith &amp; Chang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1172,1395,1339,1365]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gravata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1172,1395,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Vestalenula gravata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="17" pageNumber="546" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is more widespread, but difficult to collect.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,906,2013]" lastBlockId="18.[151,1436,151,249]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="547" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rossetti &amp; Martens" authorityYear="1998" box="[199,328,1411,1437]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,328,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Vestalenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is divided into two groups, the 
<emphasis box="[687,757,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">boteai</emphasis>
-group, which includes species with a short keel on the right valve, and the 
<emphasis box="[309,437,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">danielopoli</emphasis>
-group, consisting of species with a longer keel (
<bibRefCitation author="Rossetti, G. &amp; Martens, K." box="[965,1246,1447,1473]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" pagination="55 - 110" refId="ref15089" refString="Rossetti, G. &amp; Martens, K. (1998) Taxonomic revision of the Recent and Holocene representatives of the Family Darwinulidae (Crustacea, Ostracoda), with a description of three new genera. Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Biologie, 68, 55 - 110." type="journal article" year="1998">Rossetti &amp; Martens 1998</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<emphasis box="[1311,1381,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">boteai</emphasis>
- and 
<emphasis box="[151,279,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">danielopoli</emphasis>
-groups are both widespread, with each found in the Afrotropical, Australasian, Neotropical, Palaearctic regions, and with the 
<emphasis box="[390,460,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">boteai</emphasis>
-group also found in the Pacific Oceanic Islands region (
<bibRefCitation author="Meisch, C. &amp; Smith, R. J. &amp; Martens, K." box="[1086,1299,1519,1545]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" pagination="1 - 135" refId="ref14199" refString="Meisch, C., Smith, R. J. &amp; Martens, K. (2019) A subjective global checklist of the extant non-marine Ostracoda (Crustacea). European Journal of Taxonomy, 492, 1 - 135. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2019.492" type="journal article" year="2019">
Meisch 
<emphasis box="[1176,1232,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). Five of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rossetti &amp; Martens" authorityYear="1998" box="[151,280,1555,1581]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,280,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Vestalenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species found in 
<collectingCountry box="[480,544,1555,1581]" name="Japan" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Japan</collectingCountry>
belong to the 
<emphasis box="[708,836,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">danielopoli</emphasis>
-group of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rossetti &amp; Martens" authorityYear="1998" box="[949,1078,1555,1581]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[949,1078,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Vestalenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authority="Smith et al., 2006" box="[1096,1217,1555,1581]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornelia">
<emphasis box="[1096,1217,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">V. cornelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Straub" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[1233,1375,1555,1581]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cylindrica">
<emphasis box="[1233,1375,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">V. cylindrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith &amp; Chang, 2022" authorityName="Smith &amp; Chang" authorityYear="2022" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gravata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Vestalenula gravata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[343,432,1591,1617]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[343,432,1591,1617]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[446,537,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Neale &amp; Victor" baseAuthorityYear="1978" box="[446,533,1591,1617]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lundi">V. lundi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[591,760,1591,1617]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[591,720,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Vestalenula</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
), but it is unknown if they represent a distinct lineage within the genus. 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith &amp; Chang, 2022" authorityName="Smith &amp; Chang" authorityYear="2022" box="[272,495,1627,1653]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gravata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[272,495,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Vestalenula gravata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[502,592,1627,1653]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[502,592,1627,1653]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
lacks a post-abdomen and a pigmented eye, whereas these are present in 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith et al., 2006" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornelia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">V. cornelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[259,352,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Neale &amp; Victor" baseAuthorityYear="1978" box="[259,347,1663,1689]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lundi">V. lundi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[408,557,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Straub" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[408,553,1663,1689]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cylindrica">V. cylindrica</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The post-abdomen is a feature useful for species discrimination (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rossetti, G. &amp; Martens, K." pageId="17" pageNumber="546" pagination="55 - 110" refId="ref15089" refString="Rossetti, G. &amp; Martens, K. (1998) Taxonomic revision of the Recent and Holocene representatives of the Family Darwinulidae (Crustacea, Ostracoda), with a description of three new genera. Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Biologie, 68, 55 - 110." type="journal article" year="1998">Rossetti &amp; Martens 1998</bibRefCitation>
), but it is not clear if it is only present in particular lineages within the genus. The absence of a pigmented eye is not a widely used taxonomic character in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rossetti &amp; Martens" authorityYear="1998" box="[815,944,1735,1761]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[815,944,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Vestalenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the presence or absence of an eye is sometimes not noted in descriptions, 
<tableCitation box="[507,591,1771,1797]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="18.[151,239,296,320]" captionTargetId="figure-104@18.[151,1437,416,1745]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="TABLE 3. Characters and locations of Vestalenula species. Country codes: AU—Australia, BR—Brazil, CD—D.R. Congo, CI—Côte d’Ivoire, DE—Germany, FR—France, JP—Japan, KE—Kenya, KR—South Korea, LK—Sri Lanka, NA—Namibia, NC—New Caledonia, RO—Romania, SB—Solomon Islands, TH—Thailand, ZA—South Africa." pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Table 3</tableCitation>
), and could potentially be a homeomorphic character influenced by habitat, rather than having phylogenetic significance. The extra setae on both the antennule and antenna of 
<taxonomicName box="[1268,1436,1807,1833]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1268,1397,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Vestalenula</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
are features previously only known in three other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rossetti &amp; Martens" authorityYear="1998" box="[716,845,1843,1869]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[716,845,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Vestalenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, belonging to the 
<emphasis box="[1139,1209,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">boteai</emphasis>
-group, from 
<collectingCountry box="[1361,1433,1843,1869]" name="Brazil" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Species of the genera 
<taxonomicName authority="Rossetti &amp; Martens, 1998" authorityName="Rossetti &amp; Martens" authorityYear="1998" box="[393,791,1879,1905]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Alicenula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[393,500,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Alicenula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rossetti, G. &amp; Martens, K." box="[506,791,1879,1905]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" pagination="55 - 110" refId="ref15089" refString="Rossetti, G. &amp; Martens, K. (1998) Taxonomic revision of the Recent and Holocene representatives of the Family Darwinulidae (Crustacea, Ostracoda), with a description of three new genera. Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Biologie, 68, 55 - 110." type="journal article" year="1998">Rossetti &amp; Martens, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Brady &amp; Robertson, 1885" authorityName="Brady &amp; Robertson" authorityYear="1885" box="[804,1217,1878,1905]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Darwinula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[804,925,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Darwinula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Brady, G. S. &amp; Robertson, D." box="[931,1217,1878,1905]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" pagination="311 - 353" refId="ref12437" refString="Brady, G. S. &amp; Robertson, D. (1885) In: Jones, T. R. (Ed.), On the Ostracoda of the Purbeck Formation with notes on the Wealden species. Quarterly Journal of the Geological Society of London, 41, 311 - 353. https: // doi. org / 10.1144 / GSL. JGS. 1885.041.01 - 04.31" type="journal article" year="1885">Brady &amp; Robertson, 1885</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Rossetti &amp; Martens, 1998" authorityName="Rossetti &amp; Martens" authorityYear="1998" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Penthesilenula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1270,1436,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Penthesilenula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rossetti, G. &amp; Martens, K." box="[151,441,1915,1941]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" pagination="55 - 110" refId="ref15089" refString="Rossetti, G. &amp; Martens, K. (1998) Taxonomic revision of the Recent and Holocene representatives of the Family Darwinulidae (Crustacea, Ostracoda), with a description of three new genera. Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Biologie, 68, 55 - 110." type="journal article" year="1998">Rossetti &amp; Martens, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
have the extra setae on the antennule and antenna, while 
<taxonomicName authority="Rossetti et al., 2011" authorityName="Rossetti" authorityYear="2011" box="[1094,1436,1915,1941]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Isabenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1094,1204,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Isabenula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rossetti, G. &amp; Pinto, R. L. &amp; Martens, K." box="[1212,1436,1915,1941]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" pagination="55 - 74" refId="ref15205" refString="Rossetti, G., Pinto, R. L. &amp; Martens, K. (2011) Description of a new genus and two new species of Darwinulidae (Crustacea, Ostracoda), from Christmas Island (Indian Ocean) with some considerations on the morphological evolution of ancient asexuals. Belgian Journal of Zoology, 141 (2), 55 - 74." type="journal article" year="2011">
Rossetti 
<emphasis box="[1310,1367,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">et al.</emphasis>
, 2011
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Danielopol, 1968" authorityName="Danielopol" authorityYear="1968" box="[201,589,1951,1977]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Microdarwinula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[201,384,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Microdarwinula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Danielopol, D. L." box="[392,589,1951,1977]" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" pagination="153 - 174" refId="ref12582" refString="Danielopol, D. L. (1968) Microdarwinula n. g. et quelques remarques sur la repartition de la famille Darwinulidae Br. et Norm. (Crustacea, Ostracoda). Annales de Limnologie, 4, 153 - 174. https: // doi. org / 10.1051 / limn / 1968004" type="journal article" year="1968">Danielopol, 1968</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
only have the extra seta on the antenna. As these setae are taxonomically widespread in the family, their absence in most species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rossetti &amp; Martens" authorityYear="1998" box="[795,924,1987,2013]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[795,924,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="546">Vestalenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is possibly an apomorphy. Their loss could be a result of convergent evolution in both groups of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rossetti &amp; Martens" authorityYear="1998" box="[713,842,151,177]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="18" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[713,842,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="547">Vestalenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rossetti &amp; Martens" authorityYear="1998" box="[1004,1133,151,177]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Vestalenula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="18" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1004,1133,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="547">Vestalenula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
retaining these setae could represent a distinct phylogenetic lineage. This latter scenario would indicate that keel length, and hence the 
<emphasis box="[1357,1427,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="547">boteai</emphasis>
- and 
<emphasis box="[199,327,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="547">danielopoli</emphasis>
-groups, is not phylogenetically significant.
</paragraph>
